                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.01 Manchuria/46: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName corresp="#p_JNT1" type="from"
                            >Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-03-18T13:00:00+08:00"
                            >March 18, 1932—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received March 18—2:52 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>352. Following from American Consul General, Mukden: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“March 17, 3 p.m. <persName corresp="#p_KT2">T. Komai</persName>,
                            civilian adviser to the Kuantung Army headquarters with the rank of
                            Lieutenant General, has been appointed Director of the General Affairs
                            Department in State Affairs Council <pb facs="0702" n="598"
                                xml:id="pg_598"/> of which Premier is the head. A press report from
                            Harbin states that he will become a citizen of the new state.</p>
                        <p>Another report states that <persName corresp="#p_OC1">C.
                                Ohashi</persName>, Japanese Consul General, has been appointed
                            Director of the General Affairs Department in the Ministry of Foreign
                            Affairs. He has just returned from Tokyo.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>For the Minister:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Perkins</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
